<informationtext name="Information">
<![CDATA[
<p>Anne Todgham, Ph.D., Chairperson of the Department</p>
<h2>The Program</h2>
<p>The Department of Animal Science offers five minor programs open to students majoring in other disciplines who wish to complement their study programs with a minor in Animal Science. Some courses have required prerequisites not included as part of the minor, and students should plan accordingly.</p>
<p><strong>Advising </strong>for the minor and course offerings is located in the <a href="https://animalscience.ucdavis.edu/academics/undergrad/advising">Animal Science Advising Center</a> in 1202 Meyer Hall; 530-754-7915.</p>
<h3>Minor Advisor</h3>
<p>Russ Hovey, Ph.D., Professor</p>
]]>
</informationtext>
